♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:47.368 --> 01:49.152
LIFEGUARD

01:54.723 --> 01:56.551
BAYWATCH

02:12.132 --> 02:14.873
"NIGHTMARE BAY"

02:16.048 --> 02:18.312
[CHATTERING]

02:18.442 --> 02:20.836
[RADIO CHATTER]

02:44.164 --> 02:46.078
[LAUGHING]

02:46.209 --> 02:48.429
WHAT? THAT'S AS WET AS YOU'RE
GOING TO GET TODAY.

02:49.125 --> 02:50.909
-THORPE?
-MM-HMM.

02:51.040 --> 02:53.347
YOU WEREN'T HERE.
YOU DIDN'T SEE ME.

02:53.477 --> 02:55.827
MITCH, YOU'RE NEVER GOING
TO MAKE IT. HE'S ON THE DECK.

02:55.958 --> 02:57.177
[GROANS]

03:21.157 --> 03:22.158
[RADIO CHATTER]

03:22.289 --> 03:23.986
NO SIGN OF HIM HERE...

03:24.116 --> 03:26.510
NO OTHER OFFICE QUITE LIKE IT,
IS THERE, MITCH?

03:26.641 --> 03:29.470
-IT'S A BEAUTIFUL THING.
-THAT IT IS.

03:31.385 --> 03:32.821
WELL, NOW, YOU'VE HAD THE WEEK
TO THINK IT OVER.

03:32.951 --> 03:33.996
WHAT'S YOUR DECISION?

03:34.126 --> 03:36.259
HAVEN'T MADE IT YET.

03:37.217 --> 03:39.306
MITCH, YOU CAN'T TREAD WATER
ON THIS FOREVER.

03:39.741 --> 03:41.351
HAVE YOU TALKED IT OVER
WITH HOBIE?

03:41.482 --> 03:44.267
SURE, SURE. MY SON THINKS
IT WOULD BE A GREAT CAREER MOVE.

03:44.398 --> 03:46.661
GOOD. THAT BOY KNOWS
WHAT'S RIGHT.

03:46.791 --> 03:48.619
THE MOVE UP FROM LIEUTENANT
TO CAPTAIN

03:48.750 --> 03:51.013
WOULD MEAN A SUBSTANTIAL HIKE
IN SALARY.

03:51.143 --> 03:53.537
INCREASED RESPONSIBILITY
WITHIN THE DEPARTMENT.

03:53.668 --> 03:56.061
CAPTAIN, THE ONLY RESPONSIBILITY
I REALLY CARE ABOUT

03:56.192 --> 03:58.499
IS MAKING SURE THAT ALL THESE
PEOPLE WHO COME TO THE BEACH

03:58.629 --> 04:00.152
LEAVE SAFELY
AT THE END OF THE DAY.

04:00.283 --> 04:02.807
MITCH, THAT'S WHAT WE ALL WANT.

04:03.721 --> 04:05.288
YOU THINK I'M LOOKING FORWARD
TO BECOMING CHIEF?

04:05.419 --> 04:08.552
MOVING DOWNTOWN AWAY
FROM ALL THIS?

04:09.161 --> 04:11.468
DEALING WITH BUDGET ALLOCATIONS?

04:11.599 --> 04:12.861
NOT ON YOUR LIFE.

04:13.731 --> 04:16.038
BUT CHIEF WALLACE DECIDED
THAT I AM THE BEST QUALIFIED

04:16.168 --> 04:17.517
TO REPLACE HIM.

04:18.040 --> 04:20.608
AND I'VE DECIDED YOU'RE THE BEST
QUALIFIED TO REPLACE ME.

04:20.738 --> 04:22.087
I'M NOT.

04:22.218 --> 04:23.524
THERE ARE A LOT
OF OTHER LIFEGUARDS

04:23.654 --> 04:25.134
MUCH MORE QUALIFIED THAN ME.

04:25.265 --> 04:28.529
-NAME ONE.
-BEN.

04:28.659 --> 04:30.008
BEN?

04:30.444 --> 04:32.533
MITCH, HE IS WAY PAST HIS PRIME.

04:33.447 --> 04:35.579
BEN HAS NEVER BEEN OFF THE SAND
HIS ENTIRE CAREER.

04:35.710 --> 04:37.189
HE'S NEVER EVEN BEEN
A LIEUTENANT.

04:37.320 --> 04:38.756
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO PROMOTE HIM TO CAPTAIN?

04:38.887 --> 04:40.584
BEN'S GOT MORE EXPERIENCE
ON THIS BEACH

04:40.715 --> 04:42.194
THAN ALL THE LIFEGUARDS
PUT TOGETHER.

04:42.325 --> 04:43.848
YEAH.

04:43.979 --> 04:45.285
HE SAVED FIVE PEOPLE
THE DAY THE PIER COLLAPSED

04:45.415 --> 04:47.199
AND CRUSHED HIS LEG.

04:47.330 --> 04:49.289
MITCH, YOU KNOW, I FEEL AS BAD
ABOUT HIS INJURY AS ANYONE ELSE.

04:51.029 --> 04:53.293
I OFFERED HIM THE SWITCHBOARD.
HE'S REJECTED IT.

04:53.945 --> 04:55.686
MAYBE IF WE MAKE IT
A STEPPING STONE.

04:56.948 --> 04:59.211
SORRY, MITCH.
YOU STILL HAVEN'T NAMED ONE.

04:59.342 --> 05:01.257
LOOK, YOU GO SURF.
CLEAR YOUR HEAD.

05:01.388 --> 05:02.519
YOU'LL MAKE THE RIGHT DECISION.

05:04.260 --> 05:05.783
-OH, CAPTAIN?
-YEP?

05:06.349 --> 05:07.872
HAS THE DEPARTMENT MADE
A DECISION

05:08.003 --> 05:09.613
ON WHICH BEACH GETS A SCARAB?

05:09.744 --> 05:10.962
NOT YET.

05:11.093 --> 05:12.181
[LAUGHING]

05:12.312 --> 05:13.574
YOU OUGHT TO SEE HER, MITCH.

05:13.704 --> 05:15.445
34 FEET OF PURE VELOCITY.

05:15.576 --> 05:17.229
SLEEK AS A STINGRAY.

05:17.360 --> 05:19.231
THE MOST ADVANCED RESCUE BOAT
IN THE HISTORY

05:19.362 --> 05:20.624
OF THE LIFEGUARD SERVICE.

05:21.277 --> 05:22.626
THEY'RE LEANING TOWARDS ZUMA.

05:23.584 --> 05:25.063
-ZUMA?
-YEP.

05:25.194 --> 05:26.891
ZUMA GOT THE LAST UPGRADE!

05:27.022 --> 05:29.546
COME ON! OUR BOAT'S
ON ITS LAST LEGS.

05:30.417 --> 05:33.245
IT'S A FUNNY THING
ABOUT DECISIONS, MITCH.

05:33.376 --> 05:35.378
THEY'RE OFTEN MADE
FOR ALL THE WRONG REASONS.

05:36.118 --> 05:37.293
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

05:39.687 --> 05:40.949
ZUMA?

05:44.169 --> 05:48.130
[MUSIC PLAYING]

06:23.252 --> 06:27.865
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

06:41.226 --> 06:44.012
IT'S OKAY. I GOT YOU.

06:44.142 --> 06:46.797
YOU HURT? YOU ALL RIGHT?

06:46.928 --> 06:48.973
JUST RELAX. OKAY.

06:49.104 --> 06:50.845
I'M GOING TO TAKE YOU
IN ON THIS.

06:50.975 --> 06:53.195
PUT YOUR RIGHT ON ARM.
THAT'S GOOD.

06:53.325 --> 06:55.110
THAT'S A GIRL.
PUT YOUR LEFT ARM ON IT.

06:55.240 --> 06:57.242
OKAY, NOW ON THREE,
I'M GOING TO HOIST YOU ON.

06:57.373 --> 07:00.724
READY? ONE, TWO, THREE!

07:00.855 --> 07:03.074
THAT A GIRL. THAT A GIRL.

07:03.205 --> 07:04.598
HANG ON.

07:06.991 --> 07:09.211
ALL RIGHT. THAT A GIRL.
HERE WE GO.

07:09.341 --> 07:10.995
HERE WE GO.

07:11.126 --> 07:12.954
YOU'VE GOT IT. THAT'S IT.
COME ON, WORK YOUR ROUNDHOUSE.

07:13.084 --> 07:14.956
LET ME SEE THAT.
EVERY TIME. LET ME SEE THAT.

07:15.086 --> 07:16.871
YEAH, LEFT AND RIGHT.
LEFT AND RIGHT. YOU GOT IT.

07:17.001 --> 07:18.525
NOW, COME ON. LET'S WORK IT BACK
THIS WAY. THAT'S IT.

07:18.655 --> 07:20.091
YOU'VE GOT IT. YOU'RE ON IT.
YOU'RE ON IT.

07:20.222 --> 07:21.745
COME ON, LET'S FINISH UP
WITH SOMETHING BIG.

07:21.876 --> 07:23.660
READY? LET'S GO.
COME ON, ONE MORE TIME. NOW!

07:23.791 --> 07:25.488
COME ON, HERE IT IS.

07:25.619 --> 07:28.143
OH, EDDIE.
I AM SO SORRY, SWEETIE.

07:28.273 --> 07:30.885
-DID I HURT YOU?
-OH, NO. NO.

07:31.102 --> 07:32.669
JUST CAUGHT ME A LITTLE
OFF-GUARD, THAT'S ALL.

07:32.800 --> 07:34.802
-GOOD.
-YEAH, RIGHT, EDDIE.

07:34.932 --> 07:37.631
HEY. COME ON A MINUTE.

07:37.761 --> 07:39.459
WHAT IS THE MATTER WITH YOU?

07:39.676 --> 07:42.462
FIRST YOU HIT ME.
THEN YOU SORT OF KISS ME.

07:42.679 --> 07:44.289
WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

07:44.420 --> 07:46.291
I'M SORRY, EDDIE. IT'S NOT YOU.

07:46.683 --> 07:50.165
-WELL, THEN WHO IS IT?
-IT'S MY FATHER.

07:51.253 --> 07:53.298
HE VENTURED OFF
OUR TENNIS COURT YESTERDAY

07:53.429 --> 07:56.519
AND DECIDED TO FIND OUT EXACTLY
WHAT I DO AS A LIFEGUARD.

07:56.737 --> 07:59.087
SO HE SAT IN THE PARKING LOT
IN HIS MERCEDES

07:59.217 --> 08:00.741
AND HE SPIED ON ME.

08:01.568 --> 08:03.483
EDDIE, I WAS
RUNNING ALL DAY LONG.

08:03.613 --> 08:05.572
I MUST HAVE MADE
AT LEAST 30 PREVENTIONS.

08:05.702 --> 08:07.225
BUT YOU KNOW ALL HE SAW?

08:07.748 --> 08:09.706
HE SAW HIS LITTLE GIRL
IN A BATHING SUIT

08:09.837 --> 08:12.143
ON DISPLAY IN FRONT
OF HUNDREDS OF GUYS.

08:15.233 --> 08:16.713
HE WANTS ME TO QUIT.

08:18.672 --> 08:20.674
[MUSIC PLAYING]

08:32.033 --> 08:34.426
[SPRAY PAINT HISSING]

08:50.921 --> 08:52.749
JORDAN, DON'T DO THAT!

09:00.235 --> 09:01.976
[SIGHING]

09:40.536 --> 09:42.712
JORDAN, DON'T!
YOU'LL MAKE IT UGLY!

09:43.104 --> 09:44.540
IT AIN'T UGLY, ALL RIGHT?

09:44.758 --> 09:45.933
AND WHEN THE HOMEBOYS
COME TO THE BEACH

09:46.063 --> 09:47.587
AND SEE THEIR TAG,

09:47.717 --> 09:49.153
-I'LL BE IN TIGHT.
-I DON'T WANT YOU TO BE IN TIGHT

09:49.284 --> 09:50.981
WITH GANG BANGERS.

09:51.112 --> 09:52.722
-I DON'T WANT YOU KILLED.
-GO PLAY IN THE SAND, TIANNA.

09:52.853 --> 09:54.855
IF YOU SPRAY THOSE ROCKS
I'LL TELL MOMMY

09:54.985 --> 09:56.247
YOU CUT SCHOOL
AND TOOK ME ON THE BUS.

09:56.378 --> 09:57.553
TOOK YOU HERE?

09:57.684 --> 09:58.946
WHO EVEN ASKED YOU
TO COME WITH ME?

09:59.076 --> 10:00.687
SOMEBODY'S GOT
TO LOOK OUT FOR YOU.

10:00.817 --> 10:02.427
-GIVE ME THAT.
-LET IT GO!

10:02.558 --> 10:04.125
-GIVE IT!
-GIVE IT TO ME!

10:05.082 --> 10:05.953
JORDAN!

10:09.565 --> 10:12.002
TIANNA! TIANNA! PLEASE, TIANNA!

10:13.830 --> 10:15.745
HELP! HELP!
MY SISTER, SHE'S DROWNING!

10:15.876 --> 10:16.703
HELP!

10:18.226 --> 10:20.010
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

10:33.023 --> 10:34.459
TIANNA!

10:46.820 --> 10:48.865
OVER HERE! HELP! PLEASE HELP!

10:48.996 --> 10:50.911
OVER HERE! MY SISTER,
SHE'S DROWNING!

10:51.041 --> 10:53.348
HELP, PLEASE! OVER HERE!

10:56.090 --> 10:57.526
PLEASE COME BACK, TIANNA!

10:57.657 --> 10:59.049
GET AWAY FROM THE EDGE
OF THE ROCKS!

10:59.180 --> 11:02.052
-PLEASE!
-NOW! GET AWAY FROM THE EDGE!

11:02.183 --> 11:04.054
TIANNA! PLEASE, TIANNA!

11:04.185 --> 11:05.316
YOU SEE THAT BUILDING?

11:05.447 --> 11:06.404
YOU GO OVER THERE
AND YOU GET HELP!

11:06.535 --> 11:09.103
NOW! GO! NOW!

11:14.804 --> 11:17.589
[WAVES CRASHING]

11:50.797 --> 11:52.755
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

12:01.677 --> 12:02.983
WHAT HAPPENED?

12:03.113 --> 12:04.680
I FOUND HER FLOATING
ON SOME DEBRIS.

12:04.811 --> 12:07.291
SHE'S SUFFERING FROM SHOCK
AND EXPOSURE.

12:08.336 --> 12:09.250
WE NEED A CHOPPER UP
ABOUT TWO MILES

12:09.380 --> 12:10.991
OFF OF POINT DUME.

12:11.121 --> 12:12.514
WE'VE GOT
OTHER POSSIBLE SURVIVORS.

12:13.254 --> 12:14.821
HELP! HELP!

12:14.951 --> 12:17.214
HELP! PLEASE, HELP!
MY SISTER, SHE'S DROWNING!

12:17.345 --> 12:18.955
-HELP, PLEASE!
-WHERE?

12:19.086 --> 12:20.870
-HELP US! SHE'S OVER THERE.
-YOU TAKE CARE OF HER?

12:21.001 --> 12:22.611
GO! GO!

12:22.742 --> 12:24.700
GET IN THE BACK. JUMP IN.

13:04.871 --> 13:07.656
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

13:32.202 --> 13:33.856
-I GOT HER.
-YOU OKAY?

13:43.083 --> 13:44.998
I HAD HER BREATHING,
BUT SHE STOPPED AGAIN.

13:45.825 --> 13:48.088
-HOW LONG WAS SHE UNDER?
-AT LEAST TWO TO THREE MINUTES.

13:48.218 --> 13:50.568
-I GOT A PULSE.
-SHE'S STILL NOT BREATHING.

13:50.699 --> 13:51.874
GET HER VITALS.
I WANT THEM RECORDED.

13:52.005 --> 13:53.006
PUPILS ARE DILATED.

13:53.963 --> 13:56.487
-CAN YOU HEAR ME?
-MAINTAINING THE AIRWAY.

13:56.618 --> 13:58.141
-WHAT'S HER NAME AGAIN?
-TIANNA.

13:58.707 --> 14:01.275
TIANNA, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

14:01.405 --> 14:03.103
I'VE GOT CAPILLARY REFILL.

14:03.233 --> 14:05.018
TIANNA, IF YOU CAN HEAR ME,
MOVE YOUR FINGERS.

14:06.019 --> 14:07.672
THERE'S NO REFLEX.

14:07.803 --> 14:08.717
COME ON, TIANNA.

14:08.848 --> 14:11.067
COME ON, TIANNA.

14:11.198 --> 14:14.027
-MOVE YOUR FINGERS.
-TIANNA, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

14:16.333 --> 14:17.247
COME ON, TIANNA.

14:17.944 --> 14:18.945
COME ON, TIANNA!

14:19.075 --> 14:20.947
MOVE YOUR FINGERS.

14:22.122 --> 14:23.514
TIANNA!

14:24.124 --> 14:26.343
TIANNA, MOVE YOUR FINGERS!

14:27.910 --> 14:29.738
COME ON, TIANNA.
MOVE YOUR FINGERS.

14:33.785 --> 14:35.439
-YES.
-WE GOT HER!

14:39.530 --> 14:41.445
OKAY, BABY.

14:47.321 --> 14:49.323
EASY. OKAY, MITCH.

14:49.453 --> 14:50.454
OKAY, LET'S GO!

14:54.241 --> 14:56.243
SHE'S GOING TO BE
ALL RIGHT, ISN'T SHE?

14:56.373 --> 14:57.635
SHE SHOULD BE.

14:58.375 --> 15:00.769
I NEED A NUMBER
WHERE I CAN REACH YOUR PARENTS.

15:00.987 --> 15:03.250
IT'S ONLY MY MOM,
BUT DO YOU HAVE TO CALL HER?

15:03.380 --> 15:05.208
YEAH, SHE HAS
TO GIVE HER PERMISSION

15:05.339 --> 15:07.123
SO YOUR DOCTORS CAN TREAT
YOUR SISTER AT THE HOSPITAL.

15:07.254 --> 15:08.820
COME ON, PAL.

15:10.910 --> 15:13.390
YOU WERE GREAT OUT THERE.

15:14.565 --> 15:16.698
IT WAS ALL ON THE LINE
AND YOU CAME THROUGH.

15:17.177 --> 15:19.092
I JUST SWAM
TO THE END OF THE RIP,

15:19.222 --> 15:21.268
AND I DOVE AND SHE WAS--
THERE SHE WAS.

15:21.398 --> 15:22.747
SHE WAS RIGHT THERE, YOU KNOW?

15:22.878 --> 15:24.271
I WAS GETTING SO TIRED

15:24.401 --> 15:26.055
I COULD BARELY KEEP
MY HEAD ABOVE THE WATER.

15:26.186 --> 15:27.752
I'D LIKE TO HEAR
WHAT YOUR OLD MAN HAS TO SAY

15:27.883 --> 15:29.406
ABOUT YOU BEING A LIFEGUARD NOW.

15:35.760 --> 15:40.200
[MUSIC PLAYING]

16:06.530 --> 16:10.360
♪ WELL I TREASURE THE DAYS

16:10.491 --> 16:14.103
♪ WE WERE FEARLESS-UNAFRAID

16:14.234 --> 16:17.802
♪ WE WOULD TALK A BIG GAME

16:17.933 --> 16:22.198
♪ BUT IT DIDN'T END UP
THAT WAY ♪

16:22.329 --> 16:25.941
♪ WE WERE BOLD WE WERE BRAVE

16:26.072 --> 16:29.510
♪ BUT SOMEHOW LOST OUR WAY

16:29.640 --> 16:33.296
♪ I REMEMBER YOU'D SAY

16:33.427 --> 16:37.300
♪ WE'D BE LEGENDS ONE DAY

16:39.476 --> 16:43.263
♪ 'CAUSE ALL OUR LIVES
WE PLAYED IT SAFE ♪

16:43.393 --> 16:46.614
♪ AND IT'S OVERRATED

16:47.310 --> 16:50.922
♪ NOW IT'S TIME
TO BREAK THE CHAINS ♪

16:51.053 --> 16:54.361
♪ YEAH IT'S LIBERATING

16:54.491 --> 16:58.321
♪ LET'S GET CRAZY
LET'S CELEBRATE IT YEAH ♪

16:58.452 --> 17:02.412
♪ WE ARE WILD
AND FREE [LET'S GO] ♪

17:02.543 --> 17:06.155
♪ NO MORE WAITING
OR HESITATING TO ♪

17:06.286 --> 17:10.246
♪ SEE WHO YOU COULD BE
[LET'S GO] ♪

17:25.521 --> 17:29.439
♪ LET'S GET CRAZY
LET'S CELEBRATE IT YEAH ♪

17:29.570 --> 17:33.487
♪ WE ARE WILD
