17:37.621 --> 17:41.321
♪ SEE WHO YOU COULD BE
[LET'S GO] ♪

17:41.451 --> 17:45.107
♪ LET'S GET CRAZY
LET'S CELEBRATE IT YEAH ♪

17:45.238 --> 17:49.155
♪ WE ARE WILD
AND FREE [LET'S GO] ♪

17:49.285 --> 17:50.982
♪ NO MORE WAITING
OR HESITATING TO ♪

17:51.113 --> 17:53.072
IT STARTED OUT SO WONDERFUL.

17:54.073 --> 17:55.639
I CHARTERED A LITTLE
DIVING BOAT.

17:56.423 --> 18:00.601
THE CAPTAIN SAID THAT HE KNEW
THIS GREAT SPOT

18:00.731 --> 18:04.257
WHERE I COULD TAKE PICTURES
FOR MY CLASS ASSIGNMENT.

18:04.996 --> 18:09.479
AND HE SAID THAT HE'D CHARGE ME
WHAT I COULD AFFORD, YOU KNOW?

18:11.568 --> 18:13.614
WE WENT OUT TO A SPOT ABOUT,

18:14.702 --> 18:17.096
I DON'T KNOW,
ABOUT FOUR MILES OUT,

18:18.009 --> 18:19.315
DROPPED ANCHOR.

18:20.142 --> 18:22.318
IT WAS SO PEACEFUL DOWN THERE.

18:22.449 --> 18:24.059
SO FULL OF LIFE.

18:25.016 --> 18:27.106
WE SWAM TO A GROTTO.

18:28.672 --> 18:31.762
WALT WENT TO FIND SOME LOBSTER.

18:32.633 --> 18:34.896
HE SAID WE'D HAVE IT FOR LUNCH.

18:37.377 --> 18:39.814
I STARTED PHOTOGRAPHING
THE SEA LIFE, YOU KNOW?

18:40.336 --> 18:43.339
THE CORAL AND EVERYTHING
LOOKED SO BEAUTIFUL.

18:43.470 --> 18:45.907
I LOVED BEING THERE SO MUCH.

18:46.821 --> 18:48.562
DID HE SAY WHAT
THE SPOT WAS CALLED?

18:49.040 --> 18:51.695
SUNKEN GARDENS? CORAL CAVE?

18:51.826 --> 18:53.828
-DOES ANY OF THAT RING A BELL?
-NO. NO.

18:54.568 --> 18:56.309
BUT THERE WAS A CAVE.

18:56.918 --> 18:58.615
SOMETHING WAS IN IT.

18:58.746 --> 19:00.487
WE HEARD IT MOVING INSIDE.

19:00.617 --> 19:03.838
WALT SWAM TOWARD THE OPENING.
I STARTED TAKING PICTURES.

19:08.016 --> 19:12.238
WALT WAS AT THE ENTRANCE
SHINING HIS FLASHLIGHT INSIDE.

19:15.719 --> 19:17.547
THEN HE WAS, UH--

19:17.678 --> 19:19.201
SOMETHING GRABBED HIM

19:19.332 --> 19:22.117
AND DRAGGED HIM INTO THE CAVE.

19:22.248 --> 19:25.425
AND THEN, OH--

19:25.555 --> 19:26.730
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

19:26.991 --> 19:28.254
IT'S OKAY, LINDA.

19:29.037 --> 19:30.517
JUST TAKE YOUR TIME.

19:30.647 --> 19:32.780
I SWAM OVER TO HIM.

19:34.912 --> 19:37.785
I WAS SO SCARED,
I COULDN'T BREATHE.

19:38.742 --> 19:41.441
BUBBLES WERE GUSHING
OUT OF WALT'S TANK.

19:42.485 --> 19:44.052
IT WAS HORRIBLE.

19:44.661 --> 19:46.359
HE WAS TRYING TO BREATHE

19:46.489 --> 19:48.187
AND HE WAS KICKING.

19:49.666 --> 19:50.667
AND, UH...

19:52.582 --> 19:55.019
BUT IT HAD HIM FROM BEHIND

19:55.150 --> 19:57.805
AND HE COULDN'T GET AWAY
AND I WAS TRYING TO HELP

19:57.935 --> 19:59.502
AND I COULDN'T.

20:00.155 --> 20:01.635
WHAT HAD HIM?

20:02.636 --> 20:04.681
I DON'T KNOW.
IT WAS SOMETHING...

20:04.942 --> 20:06.857
SOMETHING MONSTROUS.

20:08.990 --> 20:11.035
AND IT WAS GREEN.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.777
IT WAS BRACKISH GREEN.

20:14.735 --> 20:16.127
THERE WERE BUBBLES.
I DON'T KNOW.

20:16.258 --> 20:17.694
THERE WERE BUBBLES ALL OVER
AND THERE--

20:17.825 --> 20:19.174
AND IT WAS DARK
AND THE CAVE WAS DARK.

20:19.305 --> 20:21.785
AND IT STARTED SWIMMING
AFTER ME.

20:23.004 --> 20:25.224
I TOOK PICTURES,
BUT I DROPPED MY CAMERA.

20:26.050 --> 20:27.443
I KNEW I HAD
TO GET OUT OF MY TANK

20:27.574 --> 20:29.097
SO I COULD SWIM FASTER.

20:29.793 --> 20:32.448
AS I WAS GETTING ON THE BOAT,
I FELT IT TOUCH ME.

20:33.057 --> 20:34.363
IT HAD MY FOOT.

20:34.842 --> 20:37.279
I PULLED IT AWAY.
I GOT ON THE BOAT.

20:38.933 --> 20:40.804
THE WATER AROUND IT
STARTED TO CHURN.

20:41.805 --> 20:44.678
I RAN TO THE BACK OF THE BOAT
TO PULL UP THE ANCHOR.

20:45.287 --> 20:48.203
IT POUNDED ON THE BOTTOM
OF THE BOAT.

20:48.899 --> 20:53.469
I PULLED THE LINE, BUT IT JUST
PULLED IT BACK INTO THE WATER.

20:55.906 --> 21:00.650
WHEN THE LINE RAN OUT, IT JUST
STARTED PULLING THE STERN UNDER.

21:01.434 --> 21:05.133
I TRIED TO GET TO THE HELM
TO GET IT STARTED.

21:08.179 --> 21:09.877
THEN SOMETHING BROKE
THROUGH THE HULL

21:10.007 --> 21:11.835
AND STARTED REACHING IN.

21:14.055 --> 21:16.492
I TRIED TO START THE ENGINE,
BUT IT JUST WOULDN'T START.

21:17.406 --> 21:19.321
THE BOAT STARTED TO SINK.

21:19.452 --> 21:21.192
I KNEW I WAS GOING TO DIE!

21:21.323 --> 21:23.325
AAH!

21:23.978 --> 21:26.241
HEY, PLEASE WAIT OUTSIDE.

21:29.026 --> 21:30.506
IT'S ALL RIGHT, LINDA.

21:30.637 --> 21:31.681
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

21:31.812 --> 21:32.856
[WHIMPERING]

21:32.987 --> 21:33.944
IT'S OKAY.

21:34.075 --> 21:35.424
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

21:36.425 --> 21:38.253
IT WAS TRYING
TO GET ME AND IT WAS--

21:38.384 --> 21:40.734
TRY AND CLOSE YOUR EYES

21:40.864 --> 21:42.692
AND I'LL BE BACK
IN JUST A MINUTE, OKAY?

21:42.823 --> 21:44.346
GOOD.

21:46.305 --> 21:47.523
WE NEED TO TALK.

21:53.834 --> 21:55.749
THIS GIRL IS A VICTIM,
NOT A STORY.

21:56.489 --> 21:59.622
IF THIS ISN'T A STORY,
THEN I DON'T KNOW WHAT IS.

21:59.753 --> 22:01.842
RESCUED AT SEA.
BOAT CRUSHED FROM BELOW.

22:01.972 --> 22:03.452
THERE WAS PROBABLY AN EXPLOSION

22:03.583 --> 22:05.367
WHICH WOULD ACCOUNT
FOR HER CONFUSED STATE.

22:05.498 --> 22:07.282
CLAIMING THAT HER COMPANION
WAS KILLED

22:07.413 --> 22:10.111
BY SOME SORT OF SEA MONSTER
IN THE SANTA MONICA BAY?

22:10.720 --> 22:13.593
LISTEN, YOU WERE HERE TO DO
A STORY ON OFFSHORE DRILLING.

22:13.723 --> 22:15.246
OH, I AM,

22:15.551 --> 22:17.423
BUT THE PUBLIC
HAS EVERY RIGHT TO KNOW

22:17.553 --> 22:19.338
IF THERE'S SOMETHING
DANGEROUS OUT THERE.

22:19.468 --> 22:21.165
THE ONLY THING DANGEROUS
OUT THERE

22:21.296 --> 22:23.080
IS GOING TO BE OIL PLATFORMS,

22:23.211 --> 22:25.126
AND THAT'S WHAT THE PUBLIC
HAS A RIGHT AND A NEED TO KNOW.

22:26.345 --> 22:27.346
JESUS.

22:38.269 --> 22:39.358
OH, EXCUSE ME.

22:39.488 --> 22:41.360
ARE YOU ALWAYS WET?

22:41.490 --> 22:43.144
AS OFTEN AS POSSIBLE.

22:43.274 --> 22:46.234
I'M KAYE MORAN. I WAS HERE
WHEN YOU BROUGHT LINDA IN.

22:46.365 --> 22:48.541
HI. I'M MITCH BUCHANNON.

22:48.671 --> 22:51.282
-IT'S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.
-THE PLEASURE'S MINE.

22:51.718 --> 22:53.459
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT THESE SEA CREATURES

22:53.589 --> 22:55.199
IN THE SANTA MONICA BAY?

22:55.330 --> 22:57.245
WELL, AS LONG AS WE DON'T
CONTINUE TO POLLUTE THE BAY,

22:57.376 --> 22:58.638
I THINK THEY SHOULD ALL SURVIVE.

22:59.639 --> 23:01.510
NO, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T MEAN SEA CREATURES.

23:01.641 --> 23:02.946
I MEANT SEA MONSTERS.

23:03.077 --> 23:04.513
SEA MONSTERS?

23:04.861 --> 23:08.082
WELL, WHO KNOWS?
I MEAN, TOXIC MUTANT JELLYFISH

23:08.212 --> 23:10.214
COULD OOZE UP ON SHORE
TO SEEK REVENGE

23:10.345 --> 23:11.564
FOR WHAT WE'VE DONE
TO THEIR ENVIRONMENT.

23:19.615 --> 23:20.964
HI.

23:24.011 --> 23:26.622
I REMEMBER THOSE EYES.

23:26.753 --> 23:28.711
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO SAVED ME.

23:30.670 --> 23:32.759
LOOK, I'M NOT CRAZY.

23:32.889 --> 23:34.369
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT CRAZY.

23:34.674 --> 23:36.502
BUT BEFORE ANY OF US JUMPS
TO ANY CONCLUSIONS,

23:36.632 --> 23:38.460
I'M GOING TO GO BACK
TO WHERE I FOUND YOU,

23:38.591 --> 23:40.331
I'M GOING TO DIVE DOWN THERE--

23:40.462 --> 23:41.811
OH, GOD. NO, DON'T.

23:41.942 --> 23:42.725
I MEAN,
IT COULD STILL BE DOWN THERE.

23:42.856 --> 23:44.466
YOU COULD GET HURT.

23:44.597 --> 23:47.382
LINDA, I KNOW SOMETHING
DOWN THERE FRIGHTENED YOU.

23:47.513 --> 23:50.472
BELIEVE ME,
WE'LL FIND OUT WHAT IT WAS.

23:50.864 --> 23:53.127
IN THE MEANTIME, YOU GOT
SOMEBODY TO PICK YOU UP?

23:54.868 --> 23:57.914
NO. I'M OUT HERE ON VACATION.
I'M FROM VIRGINIA.

23:58.045 --> 23:59.438
I'M DOWN AT THE MARINA HOTEL.

24:00.482 --> 24:02.266
WELL, IF YOU DON'T MIND,

24:02.397 --> 24:03.616
I'LL HAVE ONE OF THE LIFEGUARDS
RUN YOU BACK TO THE HOTEL.

24:05.313 --> 24:08.011
AND I'LL CALL YOU AS SOON AS
I FIND OUT WHAT'S DOWN THERE.

24:08.229 --> 24:09.883
-OKAY?
-OKAY.

24:11.362 --> 24:13.364
-THANKS.
-OKAY.

24:16.455 --> 24:17.717
DRAKE, BUDDY,
WE HAVEN'T GOT ALL DAY.

24:17.847 --> 24:19.240
CAN YOU GIVE ME
SOME MORE THROTTLE?

24:19.370 --> 24:21.590
SHE'S AN OLD LADY.
THIS IS ALL SHE'S GOT.

24:22.722 --> 24:24.724
WE BETTER GET THAT SCARAB.

24:28.858 --> 24:30.164
JUDGING CURRENTS, WIND DRIFT,

24:30.294 --> 24:32.079
AND HOW LONG LINDA
WAS IN THE WATER,

24:32.558 --> 24:34.603
OUR DIVE SPOT
SHOULD BE RIGHT HERE.

24:36.257 --> 24:37.737
DON'T THOSE OIL PEOPLE REALIZE

24:37.867 --> 24:39.652
THAT THERE'S AN ENTIRE
UNIVERSE OUT THERE

24:39.782 --> 24:41.349
MORE DIVERSE AND MAGNIFICENT

24:41.480 --> 24:43.438
THAN ANYTHING
THAT'S LEFT UP HERE?

24:43.569 --> 24:45.484
THREE-QUARTERS OF THE PLANET
IS THEIRS.

24:45.614 --> 24:48.399
THANKS. UNFORTUNATELY,
FISH CAN'T VOTE.

24:49.966 --> 24:52.229
YOU KNOW THAT GROTTO
LINDA WAS TALKING ABOUT?

24:53.143 --> 24:55.537
I THINK I DID SOME
ECHINODERMATA RESEARCH THERE,

24:55.668 --> 24:57.321
BUT I DON'T REMEMBER
THERE BEING A CAVE.

24:57.452 --> 24:59.759
-ECHINO WHAT?
-DERMATA. ECHINODERMATA.

24:59.889 --> 25:01.412
YOU KNOW,
SPINY-SKINNED ANIMALS--

25:01.543 --> 25:03.284
SEA URCHINS, STARFISH.

25:03.414 --> 25:05.242
ANY OF THOSE BIG ENOUGH
TO CRUSH A BOAT?

25:05.373 --> 25:08.376
WELL, JUST IN CASE.

25:08.507 --> 25:10.683
OH, COME ON. YOU'RE
A MARINE BIOLOGIST.

25:10.813 --> 25:12.902
DON'T TELL ME YOU BELIEVE
IN SEA MONSTERS.

25:13.033 --> 25:14.251
WHEN I WAS NINE YEARS OLD,

25:14.382 --> 25:16.079
MY DAD BOUGHT ME
A SEA MONSTER BOOK.

25:16.210 --> 25:18.517
I SAID, "DAD,
THERE'S NO SUCH THING."

25:18.647 --> 25:20.083
HE SAID, "PROVE THERE ISN'T."

25:20.214 --> 25:22.346
I'VE BEEN TRYING EVER SINCE.
I HAVEN'T YET.

25:28.657 --> 25:30.224
JUST IN CASE.

25:33.053 --> 25:35.098
[MUSIC PLAYING]

27:14.458 --> 27:16.069
[MUFFLED GASPING]

27:29.343 --> 27:31.040
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

27:33.564 --> 27:34.957
I'M SORRY TO DISTURB YOU.

27:35.088 --> 27:36.916
I JUST CAME TO SEE
HOW TIANNA WAS DOING.

27:38.308 --> 27:40.441
THIS IS THE LIFEGUARD, MOM.

27:40.571 --> 27:41.790
HI.

27:45.098 --> 27:46.665
GOD BLESS YOU.

27:46.795 --> 27:49.319
GOD BLESS YOU, CHILD,
FOR SAVING MY LITTLE GIRL.

27:50.190 --> 27:51.800
I'M JUST HAPPY THAT I WAS THERE

27:51.931 --> 27:53.280
AND SHE'S GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.

27:54.585 --> 27:56.109
I'M HAPPY YOU WERE THERE, TOO.

27:57.197 --> 27:59.590
MY BABY SHOULD HAVE
NEVER BEEN THERE.

28:01.984 --> 28:03.551
TRUTH BE KNOWN,

28:03.682 --> 28:05.814
YOU SAVED TWO LIVES TODAY.

28:06.772 --> 28:08.774
'CAUSE IF ANYTHING WOULD HAVE
HAPPENED TO MY TIANNA,

28:09.688 --> 28:11.777
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WOULD HAVE
DONE WITH THAT BOY.

28:14.388 --> 28:16.042
SARAH, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WOULD HAVE DONE

28:16.172 --> 28:18.609
IF JORDAN HADN'T BROUGHT HELP
AS FAST AS HE DID.

28:19.393 --> 28:21.395
HE GOT LUCKY TODAY.

28:21.525 --> 28:23.745
BUT THERE WON'T ALWAYS
BE SOMEONE LIKE YOU AROUND

28:23.876 --> 28:27.880
TO GET HIM OUT OF THE TROUBLE
HE IS DETERMINED TO GET INTO.

28:29.882 --> 28:31.666
LORD KNOWS, WORKING TWO JOBS,

28:32.623 --> 28:34.713
I JUST CAN'T BE
THERE ALL THE TIME.

28:38.455 --> 28:41.023
I WOULD KNOW HER JUST BY LOOKING
AT HER LITTLE HAND.

28:41.154 --> 28:44.505
IT'S ALL I LOOKED AT, JUST
WAITING FOR ONE FINGER TO MOVE.

28:48.030 --> 28:49.249
TIANNA.

28:49.945 --> 28:51.164
BABY?

28:52.252 --> 28:54.515
THIS IS THE LADY
THAT RESCUED YOU.

28:55.472 --> 28:57.213
HER NAME IS SHAUNI.

28:57.474 --> 28:58.911
ISN'T THAT A PRETTY NAME?

28:59.389 --> 29:01.087
IT'S NOT AS PRETTY AS TIANNA.

29:01.217 --> 29:02.523
THAT'S A BEAUTIFUL NAME.

29:04.699 --> 29:06.570
SHH. BABY.

29:06.701 --> 29:07.920
DON'T TRY TO TALK.

29:11.967 --> 29:14.100
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY ANYTHING,
TIANNA.

29:14.796 --> 29:18.104
YOU JUST CLOSE YOUR EYES AND YOU
TRY TO GET SOME SLEEP, OKAY?

29:27.548 --> 29:33.597
[CHATTERING]

29:36.296 --> 29:37.601
GOOD MORNING TO YOU.

29:37.732 --> 29:38.777
COULD I GET SOME MORE SYRUP,
PLEASE?

29:38.907 --> 29:40.300
THIS IS NOT GOING TO BE ENOUGH.

29:40.430 --> 29:41.867
YOU GUYS, COULD I BORROW
YOUR SYRUP, PLEASE?

29:41.997 --> 29:43.564
PASS THE JAM, PLEASE?
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

29:43.694 --> 29:45.958
CAN I HAVE YOUR SYRUP, PLEASE?
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

29:46.088 --> 29:47.350
MORE SYRUP. THANK YOU.

29:47.481 --> 29:49.091
I NEED ALL THE SYRUP
YOU GUYS GOT.

29:49.222 --> 29:50.571
I WANT TO DROWN IN IT.
NOMI, IF I START DROWNING...

29:50.701 --> 29:52.965
DO A PULL UP ON ME.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

29:53.661 --> 29:56.577
HURRY, MITCH IS COMING.
HE'S COMING. WHERE'S THE HOLE?

29:56.707 --> 29:59.319
I WANT YOU GUYS TO SMEAR ME FROM
HEAD TO TOE WITH THIS STUFF.

29:59.449 --> 30:01.277
CAN YOU DO THAT?
I WANT THIS STUFF ALL OVER ME.

30:01.408 --> 30:02.931
NOW COME ON. HE'S COMING.

30:03.062 --> 30:04.541
GET OVER HERE AND DUMP
THIS STUFF ALL OVER ME.

30:04.672 --> 30:07.675
I WANT NO AREA OF ME
THAT IS NOT COVERED.

30:07.806 --> 30:11.331
PERFECT!
GIVE ME THIS FILTHY MESS!

30:12.680 --> 30:14.943
ALL OVER. COME ON. ALL OVER.

30:19.078 --> 30:20.209
GET THE JAM.

30:23.082 --> 30:24.648
I BEAT YOU.

30:24.779 --> 30:27.738
THAT MAKES US BLADES 3,
SPOKES 2.

30:27.869 --> 30:29.044
I GOT THIS THING WON.

30:29.175 --> 30:30.741
IT'S A SEVEN-GAME SERIES, PAL,

30:30.872 --> 30:32.743
AND I'M GOING TO WIN IT
BECAUSE I'M HUNGRIER.

30:32.874 --> 30:35.834
OH, YEAH, DAD? YOU WANT TO SEE
WHO CAN EAT THE MOST PANCAKES?

30:35.964 --> 30:37.748
YOU'RE ON. LILLY?

30:37.879 --> 30:40.447
TWO STACKS OF PANCAKES
FOR THE HOBSTER AND ME.

30:40.577 --> 30:42.101
AND KEEP THEM COMING.

30:45.452 --> 30:47.019
AAH!

30:48.411 --> 30:50.239
-ARTIE.
-WHAT?

30:50.370 --> 30:52.198
IF THIS IS ANOTHER WAY
TO GET ME INVOLVED

30:52.328 --> 30:54.374
IN ONE OF YOUR CRAZY
BUSINESS SCHEMES,

30:54.504 --> 30:56.942
-FORGET IT.
-I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

30:57.159 --> 30:59.292
MY CREATOR DOESN'T RECOGNIZE
HIS OWN CREATION.

30:59.422 --> 31:00.641
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT I AM,
DO YOU?

31:00.771 --> 31:01.903
NO, BUT IF YOU WANT
TO STOP BY LATER

31:02.034 --> 31:03.383
AND DRIP ON MY PANCAKES,

31:03.513 --> 31:04.775
-THAT WOULD BE FINE.
-WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

31:04.906 --> 31:06.603
I'LL GIVE YOU
A COUPLE OF HINTS, OKAY?

31:06.734 --> 31:09.476
I'M ZSA ZSA GABOR OUT FROM ONE
LAST BEAUTY TREATMENT.

31:09.998 --> 31:11.652
-WHAT?
-LET'S SEE.

31:11.782 --> 31:13.306
I'M A JAPANESE MONSTER MOVIE.

31:13.436 --> 31:15.308
JAWZILLA. THE THING
THAT ATE BREAKFAST!

31:15.438 --> 31:18.050
HARVEY, WHAT? WHAT?
WHAT ARE YOU? WHAT?

31:18.180 --> 31:20.052
I'M A TOXIC MUTANT JELLYFISH

31:20.182 --> 31:22.358
OOZING OUT OF THE WATER
TO SEEK MY REVENGE.

31:22.489 --> 31:25.622
THE T-SHIRT RIGHTS ALONE ARE
GOING TO BE WORTH SIX FIGURES.

31:25.753 --> 31:29.017
RIGHT HERE, LIEUTENANT.
YOU MADE THE FRONT PAGE.

31:29.148 --> 31:31.454
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.
SHE QUOTED ME.

31:32.891 --> 31:35.110
-LET ME SEE THAT, WILL YOU?
-ALLOW ME, MITCH.

31:36.285 --> 31:39.810
"WHEN ASKED HIS OPINION
OF THE VICTIM'S CONTENTION

31:39.941 --> 31:41.203
THAT HER BOAT
HAD BEEN ATTACKED

31:41.334 --> 31:43.118
BY A MYSTERIOUS SEA MONSTER

31:43.249 --> 31:44.946
IN THE SANTA MONICA BAY,

31:45.294 --> 31:46.992
LIFEGUARD LIEUTENANT
MITCH BUCHANNON

31:47.122 --> 31:49.995
STATED THAT IT COULD HAVE BEEN

31:50.473 --> 31:54.303
"A TOXIC MUTANT JELLYFISH
SEEKING REVENGE

31:54.521 --> 31:57.611
FOR WHAT WE HAVE DONE
TO ITS ENVIRONMENT."

31:57.916 --> 32:00.396
DAD, COOL. CAN WE GO DIVING
AND LOOK FOR IT?

32:00.527 --> 32:02.050
NO, WE CAN'T GO DIVING
AND LOOK FOR IT.

32:02.181 --> 32:03.922
SHE QUOTED ME OUT OF CONTEXT.

32:04.052 --> 32:05.488
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED OUT THERE,
MITCH?

32:05.619 --> 32:08.013
-GO GET THE PANCAKES, WILL YOU?
-SURE, DAD.

32:08.839 --> 32:10.363
I DON'T KNOW, BEN.

32:10.493 --> 32:11.799
WAITING FOR THE CORONER'S REPORT

32:11.930 --> 32:13.540
ON THE BODY
WE PULLED UP YESTERDAY.

32:14.715 --> 32:16.456
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS PICTURE?

32:16.586 --> 32:18.980
SHOULDN'T BE IN A NEWSPAPER.
IT SHOULD BE IN A COMIC BOOK.

32:19.111 --> 32:21.113
[THORPE CHUCKLING]

32:23.158 --> 32:26.031
[CHATTERING]

32:26.161 --> 32:28.424
LOCALLY, MORE SIGHTINGS
HAVE BEEN REPORTED,

32:28.555 --> 32:30.339
ALTHOUGH NOTHING
HAS BEEN VERIFIED

32:30.470 --> 32:34.300
REGARDING THE SO-CALLED
SANTA MONICA BAY SEA MONSTER.

32:34.430 --> 32:36.519
THE IDENTITY OF THE VICTIM
HAS NOT BEEN RELEASED

32:36.650 --> 32:38.826
PENDING NOTIFICATION OF KIN.

32:44.266 --> 32:46.181
DANG, BABY?
WHAT YOU TRYING TO DO? HIT ME?

32:46.312 --> 32:48.140
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T SEE YOU RUN OUT.

32:48.270 --> 32:50.055
NAW, THAT AIN'T EVEN
GOING TO WORK. NAW, BABY.

32:50.185 --> 32:52.405
-NOT AROUND HERE.
-I WAS LOOKING FOR AN ADDRESS.

32:52.535 --> 32:53.928
IT'S 13508.

32:54.059 --> 32:55.277
BABY, WHAT YOU DOING?

32:55.408 --> 32:56.931
YOU WEARING THIS
THE WRONG SIDE OUT.

32:57.062 --> 32:58.541
AROUND HERE, RED WILL MAKE
YOU DEAD. YOU KNOW THAT?

33:00.065 --> 33:01.980
LOOK, I WAS JUST TRYING
TO FIND THIS ADDRESS.

33:02.110 --> 33:04.373
LIFEGUARD? WHAT'S THIS?
THIS AIN'T NO BEACH!

33:04.504 --> 33:05.809
THIS IS BLACKTOP,
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

33:05.940 --> 33:07.202
STOP IT. LET GO.

33:07.333 --> 33:07.986
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE FUN
WITH THIS.

33:08.116 --> 33:09.378
HEY, STOP IT.

33:09.509 --> 33:11.728
[SHOUTING]

33:11.859 --> 33:13.165
GET OFF OF ME.

33:13.295 --> 33:14.601
[SHOUTING]

33:14.731 --> 33:15.906
LET ME GO.

33:16.037 --> 33:18.344
[ENGINE REVVING]

33:23.566 --> 33:26.482
[SHOUTING]

33:26.613 --> 33:29.224
LET ME GO! STOP THE CAR!

33:30.965 --> 33:32.184
STOP IT.

33:39.147 --> 33:40.496
MAN, WHAT YOU GOT?

33:40.627 --> 33:42.063
-LET'S SEE WHAT'S INSIDE.
-GIVE IT TO ME!

33:42.194 --> 33:43.673
YOU'RE GOING TO BREAK IT.

33:43.804 --> 33:45.458
OH, I DID BREAK IT.

33:45.588 --> 33:47.634
AW, IT'S A LITTLE PONY.

33:47.764 --> 33:49.505
MY LITTLE PONY NEED A DOCTOR.

33:49.636 --> 33:50.898
-HA! HA HA!
-HEY!

33:51.029 --> 33:52.856
HEY, LEAVE HER ALONE.

33:52.987 --> 33:55.642
GET OUT OF THAT CAR RIGHT NOW
BEFORE I CRACK YOUR HEAD OPEN.

33:55.772 --> 33:58.471
-DID I BREAK IT?
-I'M SO SORRY.

33:59.559 --> 34:00.734
GIVE ME THE KEYS.

34:00.864 --> 34:02.388
GIVE THEM HERE.

34:02.605 --> 34:04.868
DARREN, YOU GET INSIDE
TILL I CALL YOUR MAMA.

34:04.999 --> 34:07.349
AND TAKE THAT RAG OFF
YOUR FOOL HEAD.

34:07.480 --> 34:09.612
NAW, NAW. YOU DO WHAT I SAY,
NOT HER.

34:09.743 --> 34:11.918
BACK ON YOUR HEAD.
AND GET ACROSS THE STREET.

34:12.789 --> 34:14.965
AND YOU, TOO. PUT YOURS ON.

34:15.531 --> 34:18.143
HE IS ONLY 12 YEARS OLD.
WHY DON'T YOU LEAVE HIM ALONE?

34:18.273 --> 34:19.492
YOU DON'T KNOW NOTHING.

34:19.621 --> 34:21.233
FREAK COME INTO OUR HOOD
WEARING RED.

34:21.362 --> 34:23.235
NAW, NAW. WITHOUT US,
HE IS ALONE.

34:23.364 --> 34:25.324
WITHOUT YOU, HE'S ALIVE.

34:25.454 --> 34:27.065
AND I'M GOING TO MAKE SURE
HE STAYS THAT WAY.

34:27.195 --> 34:29.676
NOW, YOU WANT TO TRY
TO STAB ME OR SHOOT ME?

34:29.806 --> 34:32.025
YOU OUGHT TO GET YOUR BUTT OFF
MY LAWN RIGHT NOW.

34:32.157 --> 34:35.159
MAYBE I'LL COME BY AND TAKE YOU
BY THE BEACH SOMETIME.

34:35.551 --> 34:37.639
MIGHT EVEN TAKE A RIDE
BY HERE ONE NIGHT.

34:41.643 --> 34:42.819
YO, MAN.

34:48.303 --> 34:51.176
BETTER LEAVE IT RIGHT HERE.
IT'LL BE SAFER.

34:51.306 --> 34:52.829
SHAUNI, WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL ME?

34:52.960 --> 34:55.527
I WOULD HAVE WARNED YOU
NOT TO COME DOWN HERE.

34:55.658 --> 34:57.356
I WOULD HAVE COME ANYWAY.

34:58.618 --> 35:00.272
LIFEGUARDS.

35:00.402 --> 35:02.796
YOU PROBABLY JUMP INTO
SHARK-INFESTED WATERS, TOO, HUH?

35:02.926 --> 35:05.233
THERE'S NOT ONE LIFEGUARD
WHO'S GOT ANYTHING ON YOU

35:05.364 --> 35:07.192
WHEN IT COMES TO MAKING RESCUES.

35:07.322 --> 35:10.847
YEAH, WE GOT PLENTY
OF OUR OWN SHARKS OUT HERE.

35:18.159 --> 35:20.466
I WROTE AN ACCURATE ACCOUNT
OF WHAT HAPPENED YESTERDAY.

35:20.596 --> 35:22.555
MY EDITOR'S THE ONE
WHO SENSATIONALIZED IT.

35:22.685 --> 35:23.947
I'VE ALREADY THREATENED TO QUIT

35:24.078 --> 35:25.514
IF HE DOESN'T PRINT
A RETRACTION.

35:25.645 --> 35:27.777
-RETRACTION?
-YES.

35:27.908 --> 35:29.562
YOU MEAN TWO LINES
BURIED ON PAGE EIGHT

35:29.692 --> 35:32.304
SAYING "MITCH BUCHANNON
IS NOT A COMPLETE LUNATIC?"

35:33.131 --> 35:34.741
LADY, BECAUSE OF YOU,
I'VE GOT LIFEGUARDS

35:34.871 --> 35:37.265
PULLING KOOKS WITH SPEAR GUNS
OUT OF THE SURF.

35:37.831 --> 35:39.876
WHAT YOU DID WAS
TOTALLY IRRESPONSIBLE.

35:41.182 --> 35:42.966
I'M SORRY,

35:43.097 --> 35:45.795
BUT I AM NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR ALL
THE KOOKS HERE IN LOS ANGELES.

35:46.535 --> 35:48.015
THAT'S ENDEMIC TO THIS CITY.

35:48.146 --> 35:49.843
EXCUSE ME, WILL YOU?
I GOT WORK TO DO.

35:51.149 --> 35:53.760
I JUST TOOK PHOTOGRAPHS
OF A BENT ANCHOR

35:53.890 --> 35:55.631
AND A CRUSHED SCUBA TANK.

35:56.893 --> 35:59.026
DO YOU WANT TO TELL ME
HOW THEY GOT THAT WAY?

35:59.157 --> 36:01.289
WHY WOULD I WANT
TO TELL YOU ANYTHING?

36:02.595 --> 36:04.249
BECAUSE IF YOU DON'T...

36:04.466 --> 36:06.425
THOSE PHOTOS ARE STILL
GOING TO RUN.

36:06.990 --> 36:09.036
THEN THE PUBLIC'S GOING TO HAVE
TO IMAGINE FOR THEMSELVES

36:09.167 --> 36:10.429
HOW THEY GOT THAT WAY.

36:10.559 --> 36:13.040
MITCH, YOU AND I ARE
ON THE SAME SIDE.

36:13.432 --> 36:15.216
BOTH OF US ARE AFTER THE TRUTH.

36:15.782 --> 36:17.958
I'M NOT TRYING TO EXPLOIT IT.

36:18.654 --> 36:20.047
FINE.

36:20.352 --> 36:21.744
THEN JUST TELL ME WHAT IT WAS

36:21.875 --> 36:23.485
AND THIS WHOLE THING
WILL BE OVER.

36:27.010 --> 36:28.838
YOU CAN'T, CAN YOU?

36:28.969 --> 36:30.275
OR YOU WON'T.

36:32.146 --> 36:33.321
WELL, I GUESS I'M GOING TO HAVE

36:33.452 --> 36:35.236
TO GIVE LINDA A CALL
AT HER HOTEL

36:35.758 --> 36:37.282
AND I'LL GET THE STORY FROM HER.

36:38.239 --> 36:39.806
I'LL LEAVE YOU MY CARD.

36:40.807 --> 36:44.419
WHEN YOU GET YOUR VOICE BACK,
USE IT.

36:58.172 --> 37:01.131
-MARINA HOTEL.
-LINDA HARRELSON'S ROOM, PLEASE.

37:10.619 --> 37:12.534
I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE YOU WENT
TO THAT NEIGHBORHOOD

37:12.665 --> 37:14.362
WEARING A RED JACKET.

37:14.493 --> 37:16.669
WHAT DO I KNOW ABOUT GANG
COLORS? I GREW UP IN BRENTWOOD.

37:17.278 --> 37:19.062
YOU'RE SO NAIVE.

37:19.193 --> 37:22.022
IF I RECALL, YOU DIDN'T SEEM
TO THINK SO LAST FRIDAY NI--

37:22.152 --> 37:24.851
-THAT WAS COMPLETELY DIFFERENT.
-I KNOW, AND YOU LOVED IT.

37:24.981 --> 37:27.723
DON'T CHANGE THE SUBJECT.
I'M SERIOUS.

37:28.028 --> 37:31.205
DIDN'T YOU NOTICE THAT JORDAN
WAS WEARING A BLUE BANDANNA?

37:31.336 --> 37:33.947
EDDIE, MY FOCUS WAS
ON HIS SISTER.

37:41.824 --> 37:43.435
SHAUNI. HEY.

37:44.262 --> 37:46.264
DO ME A FAVOR.

37:46.525 --> 37:47.830
DON'T DO SOMETHING LIKE
THAT AGAIN

37:47.961 --> 37:49.005
UNLESS I'M WITH YOU, OKAY?

37:49.223 --> 37:50.920
I WON'T. I JUST--

37:51.051 --> 37:52.313
I REALLY WANTED
TO GET THOSE KIDS

37:52.444 --> 37:53.662
INVOLVED IN THE WATER PROGRAM.

37:53.793 --> 37:55.142
I WANT TO DO SOMETHING FOR THEM.

37:55.273 --> 37:56.274
I KNOW.

37:57.492 --> 37:59.059
I WANT TO DO SOMETHING FOR YOU.

37:59.886 --> 38:00.930
WHAT?

38:01.714 --> 38:04.673
IT'S A NEW TECHNIQUE
IN MOUTH TO MOUTH.

38:04.804 --> 38:06.414
-OH, REALLY?
-YEAH.

38:06.545 --> 38:08.373
IT'S SOMETHING
COMPLETELY DIFFERENT.

38:09.243 --> 38:11.376
TAKES YOUR BREATH AWAY.

38:11.506 --> 38:12.942
WELL, TEACH IT TO ME.

38:32.614 --> 38:34.312
GET READY FOR THE SET.

38:37.489 --> 38:38.620
NICKY!

38:40.100 --> 38:41.623
WINCH IN THE MAIN DRAG CABLE!

38:43.799 --> 38:46.715
[WHIRRING]

38:49.849 --> 38:51.590
[CRASHING]

38:52.068 --> 38:54.201
WHAT IS IT? WHAT'S HAPPENED?

38:54.332 --> 38:57.335
[GRINDING]

38:59.337 --> 39:00.729
NET MUST HAVE SNAGGED BOTTOM!

39:00.860 --> 39:02.601
LOCK OFF THE WINCH, NICK!

39:02.731 --> 39:03.602
LOCK IT OFF!

39:07.170 --> 39:09.259
CAPTAIN! WATER OVER THE STERN!

39:10.696 --> 39:13.220
[MEN SHOUTING]

39:15.701 --> 39:19.052
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

39:27.408 --> 39:28.757
CUT THE CABLES!

39:29.236 --> 39:30.933
CUT THEM NOW!

39:37.287 --> 39:40.726
[SHOUTING]

39:50.126 --> 39:52.085
RETRIEVER

39:58.613 --> 40:00.006
MAYDAY! MAYDAY!

40:00.136 --> 40:01.790
THIS IS THE FISHING TRAWLER
"RETRIEVER."

40:01.921 --> 40:03.662
THIS IS BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

40:03.792 --> 40:06.882
STATE YOUR CONDITION AND EXACT
LOCATION, RETRIEVER. OVER.

40:07.013 --> 40:09.842
WE'RE FIVE MILES DUE WEST
OF THE PALOS VERDES PENINSULA.

40:10.930 --> 40:12.105
SOMETHING'S CAUGHT IN OUR NET!

40:14.977 --> 40:19.112
TO BE CONTINUED

40:24.639 --> 40:26.641
[ENDING MUSIC]
